{"word":"silentium","priority":"★★☆","meanings":[{"part_of_speech":"noun","gender":"neuter","definition":"静寂、沈黙、無音","english_definition":"silence, quietness, absence of sound","examples":[{"sentence":"In bibliotheca silentium servandum est.","translation":"図書館では静寂が守られなければならない"},{"sentence":"Media nocte, perfectum silentium erat.","translation":"真夜中には完全な静寂があった"}],"collocations":["silentium facere (沈黙する)","silentium imperare (沈黙を命じる)","silentium custodire (静寂を保つ)","magnum silentium (深い静寂)"],"synonyms":["quies","taciturnitas"],"antonyms":["strepitus","sonitus"]},{"part_of_speech":"noun","gender":"neuter","definition":"秘密保持、機密","english_definition":"secrecy, confidentiality","examples":[{"sentence":"De hac re silentium serva.","translation":"この件について秘密を守れ"}],"collocations":["silentium servare (秘密を守る)","silentium de aliqua re (～についての沈黙)"],"synonyms":["secretum","arcanum"],"antonyms":["divulgatio","publicatio"]}],"etymology":{"value":"ラテン語の動詞「silēre」（沈黙する）に由来し、-ium（中性名詞語尾）が付いた形。印欧祖語の*seyl-（静かな）に遡る。英語の「silence」、フランス語の「silence」などの語源となった。","priority":"★★☆"},"pronunciation":{"classical":"[sɪˈlɛn.tɪ.ʊ̃]","ecclesiastical":"[siˈlɛn.tsi.um]","syllables":"si-len-ti-um"},"inflection":{"declension":"2nd declension","case_forms":{"nominative":"silentium","genitive":"silentiī","dative":"silentiō","accusative":"silentium","ablative":"silentiō","vocative":"silentium"},"plural_forms":{"nominative":"silentia","genitive":"silentiōrum","dative":"silentiīs","accusative":"silentia","ablative":"silentiīs","vocative":"silentia"}},"usage_notes":{"explanation":"「silentium」は主に2つの意味で用いられる：(1)物理的な静けさ・無音状態、(2)情報を口外しないこと（秘密保持）。格言や標語でよく使われ（例：「Silentium est aureum」＝「沈黙は金」）、命令形で「沈黙せよ」の意味（「Silentium!」）でも用いられる。英語の「silence」に相当するが、より文語的・格式ばった表現。","priority":"★★☆"},"common_mistakes":{"examples":[{"incorrect":"✗ Silentium est bonum in ecclesia.","correct":"✓ Silentium in ecclesia bonum est.","note":"ラテン語では通常、動詞が文末に来る。形容詞も名詞の後に置かれることが多い。"}],"priority":"★☆☆"},"related_words":{"derivatives":["silens (形容詞: 静かな)","silenter (副詞: 静かに)","silentiosus (形容詞: 静かな)","silentio (動詞: 沈黙させる)"],"idioms_phrases":["Silentium est aureum (沈黙は金)","Silentium! (静粛に！)","sub silentio (密かに)"],"priority":"★★☆"},"level_frequency":{"frequency":"中頻度 (中級ラテン語テキストでよく出現)","priority":"★☆☆"},"readability_explanation":{"level":"中級ラテン語","text":"「silentium」はラテン語の中級レベルの単語で、「静寂」や「沈黙」を意味します。名詞の第2変化中性名詞で、格変化を覚える必要があります。日常会話よりも文学作品や格言、公文書などでよく見かけます。英語の「silence」と同源なので、比較的意味を推測しやすい単語です。"},"example_sentences":[{"sentence":"Post tumultum, dulce silentium sequitur.","translation":"騒動の後には甘美な静寂が続く","type":"noun","meaning_category":"静寂"},{"sentence":"Silentium de re publica servavit.","translation":"彼は国家の件について沈黙を守った","type":"noun","meaning_category":"秘密保持"},{"sentence":"Magister silentium in classe imperavit.","translation":"教師は教室で沈黙を命じた","type":"noun","meaning_category":"静寂"}]}